.Dd 17/04/26
.Dt visdiff 1
.Os Darwin
.Sh NAME
.Nm visdiff
.Nd compare two files or two folders with VisualDiffer
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl -wait
.Op Fl -focus
.Op Fl -no-warning
.Op Fl -version
.Ar left\ file\ or\ folder
.Ar right\ file\ or\ folder
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
opens a VisualDiffer comparison between two paths.
The left and right arguments must both be files or both be folders.
.Pp
Relative paths require the caller shell to provide
.Ev PWD .
If
.Ev PWD
is not available,
.Nm
cannot safely resolve relative paths because the tool is sandboxed.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "--no-warning"
.It Fl -wait
wait until the diff window is closed before returning
.It Fl -focus
restore the caller application focus after waiting
This option is valid only when
.Fl -wait
is also used
.It Fl -no-warning
suppress the sandbox warning message
.It Fl -version
show the application version and exit
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Lk https://wiki.visualdiffer.com/unixshell.html
